I have now thoroughly explored the entire codebase. Let me compile the comprehensive implementation plan.

---

# Comprehensive Implementation Plan: Wattpad-like "Stories" Feature for iskrib_v3

## 1. DATABASE SCHEMA (SQL for Supabase/PostgreSQL)

```sql
-- ============================================================
-- STORIES FEATURE: Complete Database Schema
-- ============================================================

-- 1a. Stories table
CREATE TABLE stories (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    author_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    title TEXT NOT NULL,
    description TEXT DEFAULT '',
    cover_url TEXT DEFAULT NULL,
    status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'ongoing' CHECK (status IN ('ongoing', 'completed', 'hiatus')),
    genre TEXT DEFAULT NULL,
    tags TEXT[] DEFAULT '{}',
    is_mature BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT false,
    privacy TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'public' CHECK (privacy IN ('public', 'private')),
    read_count INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
    vote_count INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
    created_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
    updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
);

CREATE INDEX idx_stories_author ON stories(author_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_stories_status ON stories(status);
CREATE INDEX idx_stories_created ON stories(created_at DESC);
CREATE INDEX idx_stories_privacy ON stories(privacy);
CREATE INDEX idx_stories_genre ON stories(genre);

-- 1b. Chapters table
CREATE TABLE chapters (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    story_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES stories(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    chapter_number INTEGER NOT NULL,
    title TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'Untitled Chapter',
    content JSONB DEFAULT NULL,                       -- Lexical JSON state
    word_count INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
    status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'draft' CHECK (status IN ('draft', 'published')),
    published_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NULL,
    created_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
    updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
    UNIQUE(story_id, chapter_number)
);

CREATE INDEX idx_chapters_story ON chapters(story_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_chapters_story_number ON chapters(story_id, chapter_number);
CREATE INDEX idx_chapters_status ON chapters(status);

-- 1c. Paragraph-level comments (Option C: hybrid index + text fingerprint)
CREATE TABLE story_comments (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    chapter_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES chapters(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    parent_id UUID DEFAULT NULL REFERENCES story_comments(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    comment TEXT NOT NULL,
    paragraph_index INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT -1,      -- -1 = chapter-level comment
    paragraph_fingerprint TEXT DEFAULT NULL,           -- first 100 chars of paragraph text content
    created_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
);

CREATE INDEX idx_story_comments_chapter ON story_comments(chapter_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_story_comments_paragraph ON story_comments(chapter_id, paragraph_index);
CREATE INDEX idx_story_comments_user ON story_comments(user_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_story_comments_parent ON story_comments(parent_id);

-- 1d. Story votes (likes for stories, similar to existing likes table)
CREATE TABLE story_votes (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    story_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES stories(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    created_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
    UNIQUE(story_id, user_id)
);

CREATE INDEX idx_story_votes_story ON story_votes(story_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_story_votes_user ON story_votes(user_id);

-- 1e. Reading progress tracking
CREATE TABLE reading_progress (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    user_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    story_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES stories(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    chapter_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES chapters(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    scroll_position REAL DEFAULT 0,                   -- 0.0 to 1.0 percentage
    last_read_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
    UNIQUE(user_id, story_id)
);

CREATE INDEX idx_reading_progress_user ON reading_progress(user_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_reading_progress_story ON reading_progress(user_id, story_id);

-- 1f. Story library (user's reading list / bookmarked stories)
CREATE TABLE story_library (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    user_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    story_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES stories(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    added_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
    UNIQUE(user_id, story_id)
);

CREATE INDEX idx_story_library_user ON story_library(user_id);

-- 1g. RPC: increment story read count
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION increment_story_read_count(s_id UUID)
RETURNS void AS $$
BEGIN
    UPDATE stories SET read_count = read_count + 1 WHERE id = s_id;
END;
$$ LANGUAGE plpgsql;

-- 1h. Trigger: auto-update updated_at on stories
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION update_story_timestamp()
RETURNS TRIGGER AS $$
BEGIN
    NEW.updated_at = now();
    RETURN NEW;
END;
$$ LANGUAGE plpgsql;

CREATE TRIGGER stories_updated_at
    BEFORE UPDATE ON stories
    FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION update_story_timestamp();

CREATE TRIGGER chapters_updated_at
    BEFORE UPDATE ON chapters
    FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION update_story_timestamp();
```

## 2. API ENDPOINTS

### Stories CRUD
| Method | Path | Auth | Description |
|--------|------|------|-------------|
| `POST` | `/api/stories` | `requireAuth` | Create a new story (title, description, cover image via multer) |
| `GET` | `/api/stories` | `optionalAuth` | Browse/discover stories (pagination, filter by genre/status, sort by newest/popular) |
| `GET` | `/api/stories/:storyId` | `optionalAuth` | Get single story with chapter list and metadata |
| `PATCH` | `/api/stories/:storyId` | `requireAuth` | Update story metadata (title, description, cover, status, genre, tags) |
| `DELETE` | `/api/stories/:storyId` | `requireAuth` | Delete story and all chapters |
| `GET` | `/api/stories/search` | none | Search stories by title/description |
| `GET` | `/api/stories/user/:userId` | `optionalAuth` | Get all stories by a user |
| `GET` | `/api/stories/my` | `requireAuth` | Get current user's stories (includes drafts) |

### Chapters CRUD
| Method | Path | Auth | Description |
|--------|------|------|-------------|
| `POST` | `/api/stories/:storyId/chapters` | `requireAuth` | Create a new chapter |
| `GET` | `/api/stories/:storyId/chapters` | `optionalAuth` | List all published chapters of a story |
| `GET` | `/api/stories/:storyId/chapters/:chapterId` | `optionalAuth` | Get single chapter content |
| `PATCH` | `/api/stories/:storyId/chapters/:chapterId` | `requireAuth` | Update chapter (content, title, status) |
| `DELETE` | `/api/stories/:storyId/chapters/:chapterId` | `requireAuth` | Delete chapter |
| `POST` | `/api/stories/:storyId/chapters/reorder` | `requireAuth` | Reorder chapters (send array of {chapterId, newNumber}) |

### Interactions
| Method | Path | Auth | Description |
|--------|------|------|-------------|
| `POST` | `/api/stories/:storyId/vote` | `requireAuth` | Toggle vote on a story |
| `POST` | `/api/stories/:storyId/library` | `requireAuth` | Add/remove story from reading library |
| `POST` | `/api/stories/:storyId/chapters/:chapterId/comment` | `requireAuth` | Add paragraph-level or chapter-level comment |
